('25834', '1', 'Using a thin sharp knife, cut the corn kernels from the cobs and transfer them to a bowl. Working over the bowl to catch the liquid, scrape the corn milk from the cobs with the back of a knife.'),
('25834', '2', 'In a large soup pot, melt the butter in the oil.'),
('25834', '3', 'Add the shallots and cumin seeds and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the shallots are translucent, about 5 minutes.'),
('25834', '4', 'Add the corn and cook for 1 minute.'),
('25834', '5', 'Add the vegetable stock and cook for 25 minutes.'),
('25834', '6', 'Working in batches, puree the soup in a blender until smooth. Pass the soup through a fine sieve, pressing to extract as much pulp as possible. Rinse out the soup pot and return the soup to it.'),
('25834', '7', 'Add the cream and season with salt and white pepper.'),
('25834', '8', 'In a large skillet, heat the olive oil until shimmering.'),
('25834', '9', 'Add the shiitakes and cook over moderately high heat until softened, about 4 minutes.'),
('25834', '10', 'Add the shallot and garlic, season with salt and pepper and cook for 1 minute. Stir in the stock and cook until the shiitakes are dry, about 3 minutes.'),
('25834', '11', 'Transfer to a plate to cool.'),
('25834', '12', 'In a bowl, combine the mayonnaise, egg, mustard, cayenne and 1 teaspoon of the chives. Fold in the shiitakes and the crabmeat and then the bread crumbs. Shape rounded tablespoons of the mixture into 18 small crab cakes and transfer to a baking sheet lined with lightly floured wax paper; refrigerate until firm.'),
('25834', '13', 'Reheat the soup. Meanwhile, dust the crab cakes with flour, tapping off any excess. Melt the butter in a large nonstick skillet.'),
('25834', '14', 'Add the crab cakes and cook over moderately high heat until browned and crisp, about 2 minutes per side.'),
('25834', '15', 'Transfer the crab cakes to a paper-towel-lined plate and season with salt.'),
('25834', '16', 'Ladle the soup into shallow soup plates and arrange 3 crab cakes in each plate. Sprinkle with the remaining 1 teaspoon chives and serve.'),
('25838', '1', 'Special equipment: cookie cutter (3-inch)'),
('25838', '2', 'Melt butter in saute pan, add in corn, red bell pepper and onion.'),
('25838', '3', 'Let saute until onion is translucent and corn has released some of it''s sugars.'),
('25838', '4', 'Add in 1/2 of the basil leaves and a couple of twists of black pepper.'),
('25838', '5', 'Add in 1/4 cup heavy cream and reduce by half. Set aside to cool.'),
('25838', '6', 'When cool, smash up a bit with a fork, stir in ricotta and cream cheese.'),
('25838', '7', 'Place wonton wrappers down (three at a time works) and in the center of each, place 1 1/2 t filling.'),
('25838', '8', 'Brush exposed wrapper with egg yolk, carefully place a second wrapper on top and carefully seal edges, making sure to get out any air bubbles.'),
('25838', '9', 'Cut with star cutter, work fingers around edges to make sure seal is tight. Set aside on floured baking sheet and continue to assemble.'),
('25838', '10', 'When finished, boil water and gently add raviolis a few at a time, cooking for 2 minutes or until they float. Carefully remove and drain.'),
('25838', '11', 'For Sauce: In clean saute pan, melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter, when melted, add in remaining basil, saute until crisp and butter is just very lightly browning.'),
('25838', '12', 'Add in remaining cream and reduce to thickened. Salt and pepper to taste, serve over raviolis immediately.'),
('25838', '13', 'Garnish with Parmesan.'),
('25839', '1', 'In a large bowl, toss all of the vegetables together and set aside at room temperature.  Do not refrigerate.'),
('25839', '2', 'When ready to serve, in large skillet, render the bacon until crisp.'),
('25839', '3', 'Add the chile powder and stir.'),
('25839', '4', 'Add the vinegar and bring to a simmer.'),
('25839', '5', 'Add the herbs.'),
('25839', '6', 'Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss.'),
('25839', '7', 'var article'),
