('25873', '10', 'article'),
('25873', '11', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('25877', '1', 'Place the avocado in the bottom of a nonreactive mixing bowl and gently toss it with 2 tablespoons of the lime juice. Spoon the tomato on top of the avocado.'),
('25877', '2', 'Cut the kernels off the corn. The easiest way to do this is to lay the cob flat on a cutting board and remove the kernels using lengthwise strokes of a chef''s knife.'),
('25877', '3', 'Add the corn kernels to the mixing bowl. The salsa can be prepared to this stage up to 2 hours ahead. Refrigerate it, covered.'),
('25877', '4', 'Just before serving, add the jalapeño(s) and cilantro to the mixing bowl and gently toss to mix. Taste for seasoning, adding more lime juice as necessary and season with salt and pepper to taste; the salsa should be highly seasoned.'),
('25880', '1', 'Build a charcoal fire in an outdoor grill.'),
('25880', '2', 'Pull off most of the corn husks, leaving only a double layer of husk attached.'),
('25880', '3', 'Remove and discard the silk.'),
('25880', '4', 'Using a food processor fitted with the metal blade, pulse together all the ingredients, except the butter, until finely chopped.'),
('25880', '5', 'Add the butter and pulse until smooth.'),
('25880', '6', 'Spread a light film of paste over the kernels and replace the attached husks.'),
('25880', '7', 'When the coals are dusty and glowing, grill the corn, turning often, for about 10 minutes until the husks are lightly charred.'),
('25880', '8', 'Serve the corn in their husks.'),
('25881', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly spray a baking sheet with olive oil cooking spray; set aside.'),
('25881', '2', 'In a microwave-safe bowl, combine corn, mushrooms, pimentos, garlic, parsley, 1 teaspoon herbs, and vinegar.'),
('25881', '3', 'Mix thoroughly and set aside.'),
('25881', '4', 'Cut salmon into 4 serving portions. Sprinkle remaining herbs on a plate. Use a pastry brush to brush salmon with olive oil.'),
('25881', '5', 'Coat salmon with herbs and place fillets on prepared baking sheet.'),
('25881', '6', 'Bake in preheated oven for 22 to 26 minutes.'),
('25881', '7', 'Cover corn mixture and heat in microwave on HIGH for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.'),
('25881', '8', 'Serve salmon immediately over corn mixture.'),
('25883', '1', 'In a large saucepan, heat together the coconut milk, canned corn and sugar over medium heat, about 10 minutes.'),
('25883', '2', 'Add the condensed milk and continue over medium heat for about five minutes.'),
('25883', '3', 'In a bowl, stir together the half and half and corn starch until smooth.'),
('25883', '4', 'Add the corn starch/milk mixture to the saucepan and cook for another 8-12 minutes.  The mixture should thicken slowly towards the end of the cooking time.'),
('25883', '5', 'Take off the heat and pour into a glass baking dish or into separate glasses.  Leave to cool to room temperature before chilling for a few hours (or overnight) in the refrigerator.'),
('25883', '6', 'Garnish with toasted shredded coconut and/or fresh corn before serving.'),
('25886', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('25886', '2', 'Fill a huge stockpot, preferably fitted with a basket insert, with about 4 quarts of water. Keep in mind that when you add the solid ingredients the water level will rise, so don''t fill the pot up more than halfway. Squeeze the lemons into the water, tossing in the halves too.'),
('25886', '3', 'Add the bay leaves, salt, seasoning, thyme, onions, chiles and garlic; bring the broth to a boil over medium-high heat and simmer for 10 minutes. You want a very aromatic broth with plenty of salt and spices. Taste it; don''t be afraid to make it strong so some of the flavor can penetrate and get absorbed by the potatoes and other ingredients. Adjust seasoning with salt.'),
('25886', '4', 'Add the potatoes to the pot to give them a head start; simmer for 20 minutes. Now add the corn and sausage; cook another 5 minutes, making sure everything stays covered with the liquid.'),
('25886', '5', 'Add the clams and boil for 8 to 10 minutes until they open. Then toss in the shrimp and shut off the heat. Cover the pot and let the shrimp steep in the flavor for 15 minutes.'),
('25886', '6', 'Drain and spread the shrimp, sausage, clams, corn, potatoes, and onions out on a newspaper-covered table.'),
('25886', '7', 'Serve with lemons and plenty of napkins. Reserve the broth to make Shrimp Cocktail Shots.'),
('25894', '1', 'Heat oven to 450F and arrange a rack in the middle.'),
('25894', '2', 'Brush tortilas on both sides with a bit of the oil then toast until just golden brown, about 5 minutes. Meanwhile, add enough oil to a nonstick large skillet to coat the bottom then heat over medium-high heat.'),
('25894', '3', 'When the oil shimmers, add the onion, stir, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and cook until soft, about 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('25894', '4', 'Add the garlic, poblano, and zucchini and cook until poblano is soft and zucchini is golden brown, another 5 minutes.'),
('25894', '5', 'Assemble the pizzas by putting a few spoonfuls of black beans on the bottom of the toasted tortillas.'),
('25894', '6', 'Add the zucchini mixture, top with a bit of crumbled cheese and place back in the oven until the tortillas are brown and the cheese is melted, about 5 to 10 minutes.'),
('25894', '7', 'If desired, char the corn over an open flame or grill (you can have it raw too). Trim the corn kernels off the cob and, if using, top each pizza with a bit of the corn. Top with salsa, avocado, and some cilantro leaves and serve.'),
('25895', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('25895', '2', 'Butter the baking pan.'),
('25895', '3', 'In a mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.'),
('25895', '4', 'Add the liquid ingredients and mix well.  Fold in the vegetables.'),
('25895', '5', 'Pour the batter into the pan and bake for 35 minutes, or until the edges turn golden and pull away from the sides of the pan.'),
('25895', '6', 'var article'),
('25895', '7', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('25895', '8', 'article'),
('25895', '9', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('25899', '1', 'Using a sharp knife, cut the corn kernels from the cobs and reserve in a large bowl.'),
('25899', '2', 'Using a spoon, scrape the milky liquid from the cob into the bowl of kernels.'),
('25899', '3', 'Thinly slice the cabbage and chop medium fine.'),
('25899', '4', 'Cut the green and red peppers into thin strips and dice.'),
('25899', '5', 'Chop the onions.'),
('25899', '6', 'In the kettle, bring 1 quart of the vinegar to a simmer over moderate heat.'),
('25899', '7', 'Whisk in the flour, sugar, salt, dry mustard, and turmeric.'),
('25899', '8', 'Add the remaining 1 quart vinegar and simmer for 30 minutes.'),
('25899', '9', 'Ladle the relish into sterilized jars and seal.'),
('25899', '10', 'var article'),
('25899', '11', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('25899', '12', 'article'),
('25899', '13', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('25900', '1', 'In a large saucepan, place the shrimp in 2 quarts of cold water.'),
('25900', '2', 'Add the bay leaf, peppercorns, and the halved and squeezed lemon.  Bring to a boil over moderately high heat.'),
('25900', '3', 'Add the corn and remove from the heat.'),
('25900', '4', 'Drain and turn into a serving bowl.'),
('25900', '5', 'Remove and discard the halved lemon and bay leaf. Fold in the scallions and lemon slices.'),
('25900', '6', 'Make the vinaigrette and pour over the corn and shrimp, tossing to coat.'),
('25900', '7', 'Let stand for 15 minutes.  Season to taste with salt and serve warm.'),
