('25917', '1', 'Measure chili powder, ancho chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt, red pepper flakes and bay leaves into a small dish. Rinse and drain beans (if using canned beans). Pull out food processor and toss in garlic cloves.'),
('25917', '2', 'Heat olive oil in a soup pot over medium high heat.'),
('25917', '3', 'Add onion, garlic, and celery mixture. Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until soft.'),
('25917', '4', 'Add turkey, break up with a spoon. Cook, stirring occasionally, until turkey is cooked through and no pink is showing.'),
('25917', '5', 'Add spices, cook for 1 minute, stirring continuously. Toss in beans, broth, tomato sauce, and crushed tomatoes.'),
('25917', '6', 'Add in corn, cook uncovered an additional 15 minutes.'),
('25917', '7', 'Garnish with fresh chopped cilantro and red onion or shallot. Enjoy!'),
('25918', '1', 'Rinse the rice in plenty of cold water.'),
('25918', '2', 'Add to a saucepan with 1 pint of cold water. Bring to the boil. Reduce to a simmer, add a lid and cook about 10/15 mins until liquid has been absorbed and the rice is cooked. Fork through the grains and leave to one side.'),
('25918', '3', 'Heat the oil in a large wok or frying pan. Cook the onion ringson a medium heat until crisp.'),
('25918', '4', 'Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper. These wil be used for the garnish.'),
('25918', '5', 'In the same pan and using the remaining oil, cook the second onion. When softened, add the chillies , ginger and garlic. Cook for a couple of minutes.'),
('25918', '6', 'Add the grated carrots, bean sprouts, peas etc. Stir through.'),
('25918', '7', 'Add the paprika and stir through. cook for about 3 mins.'),
('25918', '8', 'Next is to add the cooked rice and stir through the vegetables. Keep stiring until everything is mixed well.'),
('25918', '9', 'Next, stir the tomato ketchup and soy sauce together with the water and add to the rice and vegetables. Cook over a medium heat for about 5 mins.'),
('25918', '10', 'Serve with the onion rings on the top.'),
('25919', '1', 'In a large soup pot combine the onion, chicken, celery, tomatoes with liquid, carrots, broth, corn, peas and zucchini. Stir together and simmer over medium low heat for 1/2 hour, or until vegetables are cooked and tender.'),
('25923', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('25923', '2', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish with cooking spray. Set aside.'),
('25923', '3', 'In a small bowl beat 1 egg with the chicken broth. In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients and egg mixture. Stir to combine.'),
('25923', '4', 'Transfer to the prepared casserole dish.'),
('25923', '5', 'Bake for 1 hour.'),
('25927', '1', 'In a bowl, combine fruit, jalapeno, sugar, cornstarch, and cinnamon. Stir to coat and let set for 1 hour.'),
('25927', '2', 'Set up grill for direct cooking over medium heat. In a bowl, blend together 1/4 cup of butter and sweet corn cake mix with a fork until crumbly. Set aside.'),
('25927', '3', 'Place remaining 1/4 cup butter in a 10-inch cast iron skillet (or other oven-proof skillet) and set on hot grill. When butter has melted, add fruit mixture. Stir to combine. Sprinkle the corn cake mixture to cover thefruit. Cover grill and cook 20 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and caramelized around the edges of the pan.'),
('25927', '4', 'Remove from grill and let cool.'),
('25927', '5', 'Serve warm with a scoop of ice cream or a dollop of whipped topping.'),
('25927', '6', 'INDOOR: Prepare fruit mixture as directed. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly spray 4 ramekins with cooking spray; set aside. Prepare corn topping mixture as directed. Spoon fruit mixture into prepared ramekins and sprinkle with corn topping mixture.'),
('25927', '7', 'Bake for 45 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.'),
('25927', '8', 'Serve as directed.'),
('25928', '1', 'Put the couscous in a small saucepan.'),
('25928', '2', 'Add 1/2 of the boiling chicken stock and enough water to cover. Simmer for 3 minutes, remove from heat and set aside.'),
('25928', '3', 'In a large skillet or wok, heat the butter/margarine until it sizzles.'),
('25928', '4', 'Add the chicken breasts and saute until lightly browned.'),
('25928', '5', 'Add the other 1/2 of the chicken stock and the cream and heat gently until just boiling.'),
('25928', '6', 'Mix in the corn, tomatoes and 1/2 of the fresh tarragon.'),
('25928', '7', 'Heat through for 1 minute and season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('25928', '8', 'With a fork fluff up reserved couscous.'),
('25928', '9', 'Add a handful of tarragon and the lemon juice. Salt and pepper to taste. Spoon the couscous and chicken onto serving plates and garnish with the remaining tarragon.'),
('25929', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.'),
('25929', '2', 'Season short ribs with salt, pepper, and seasoning mix.'),
('25929', '3', 'Heat a large roasting pan with lid over medium high heat and add oil. Sear ribs in hot oil on all sides until well browned.'),
('25929', '4', 'Remove from roasting pan and set aside.'),
('25929', '5', 'Add peppers, onions, celery and garlic and cook until well browned. Deglaze roasting pan with red wine, then add barbeque sauce and stock and bring to a boil. Return ribs to roasting pan and cover tightly with foil.'),
('25929', '6', 'Place in preheated oven and braise for 2 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender when pierced with a fork.'),
('25929', '7', 'Remove ribs from sauce and keep warm. Skim fat from the top of sauce and season with salt and pepper.'),
('25929', '8', 'Pour sauce over short ribs and serve with horseradish mashed potatoes and sweet corn salad with basil vinaigrette.'),
('25931', '1', 'Melt butter in 3-qt. saucepan on medium heat.'),
('25931', '2', 'Add flour; stir with wire whisk until well blended.  Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended.  Stir in water. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.'),
('25931', '3', 'Add cheese; cook until cheese is completely melted, stirring constantly.  Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.  Reduce heat to medium-low.'),
('25931', '4', 'Simmer 10 min. or until heated through, stirring occasionally.'),
('25932', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix together balsamic vinegar, oil, salt, sugar, black pepper, cumin, and chili powder.'),
('25932', '2', 'In a medium bowl, stir together black beans and corn. Toss with vinegar and oil dressing, and garnish with cilantro.  Cover, and refrigerate overnight.'),
('25933', '1', 'Combine the chicken, vegetables, corn, scallions, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.'),
('25933', '2', 'Mix well. Ready to serve!'),
('25935', '1', 'Fry bacon over medium-high heat in a Dutch oven until crisp, 7 to 8 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate.'),
('25935', '2', 'Pour off all but 2 Tbs. of the bacon drippings.'),
('25935', '3', 'Add onions; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('25935', '4', 'Add lima beans, 1/2 cup water, salt and pepper, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and continue to simmer, covered, until partially cooked, about 5 minutes.'),
('25935', '5', 'Add corn, cream, and thyme; return to a simmer, and warm until vegetables are fully cooked and cream doesn''t pool, about 5 minutes longer. (Can be refrigerated at this point up to 2 days ahead.)'),
('25935', '6', 'When ready to serve, stir bacon and chives into warm succotash. This recipe doubles easily.'),
('25938', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400F. Butter a 3-quart shallow tinlined pan or porcelain casserole dish and dust with flour. Shake out any excess.'),
('25938', '2', 'Place the kernels and pulp in a food processor and pulse on and off until the kernels are lightly crushed. Set aside.'),
('25938', '3', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the milk and cream and scald over medium heat.'),
('25938', '4', 'In a medium saucepan, melt the butter. When the foam subsides, remove from the heat and whisk in the flour until smooth.'),
('25938', '5', 'Whisk in the cream mixture. Cook, whisking constantly, until the mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.'),
('25938', '6', 'Remove from the heat, fold in the crushed corn mixture, mace, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('25938', '7', 'Using an electric mixer on high speed, beat the egg yolks for about 5 minutes until thick and lemon colored.'),
('25938', '8', 'In a separate bowl, combine the egg whites with a pinch of salt. Beat the whites until they form stiff glossy peaks.'),
('25938', '9', 'Mix the yolks into the corn mixture, then fold in a large spoonful of the egg whites. Gently fold in the remaining whites. (Do not overblend; streaks of white should be visible.)'),
('25938', '10', 'Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish and bake for 15 minutes until puffed and lightly golden on top.'),
('25938', '11', 'Serve immediately.'),
('25940', '1', 'Cut a round lid in the top of the large pumpkin.  The stem will serve as the handle.  Scoop out the seeds and loose fiber.  Return the lid and set aside.'),
('25940', '2', 'The soup:  Seed the smaller pumpkin and dice the flesh into -inch cubes.  Measure out 1 cup of flesh and reserve the remainder for another use.'),
('25940', '3', 'Remove the outer skin; reserve.  In a large kettle, bring 1 quart of the chicken stock to a boil over high heat.  Reduce the heat, add the chicken breast and simmer until cooked through.'),
('25940', '4', 'Removed with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool.'),
('25940', '5', 'When cool enough to handle, discard the skin and bones and shred the meat.  Skim off any foam from the top of the stock.  Bring the stock back to a mild boil and cook the butter beans until almost tender.'),
('25940', '6', 'Remove the beans with a slotted spoon and reserve.  Bring the stock back to a mild boil and cook the butter beans until almost tender.'),
('25940', '7', 'Remove with a slotted spoon and reserve.'),
('25940', '8', 'Pour the remaining  quart chicken stock into a large pot. Strain the poaching stock through a fine mesh sieve into the large pot of stock.  Bring the stock to a light boil and add the cornichons, baby corn, peppers, and tomatoes. Simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('25940', '9', 'Add the scallions, the reserved beans, pumpkin, fruits, and shredded chicken and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('25940', '10', 'Check for seasonings and add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('25940', '11', 'Pour the soup into the pumpkin tureen and serve.'),
